<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1451,666,795]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">
A species easily separated from all other Thai species by the characteristic pilose indumentum of remarkably long [1–2(–3) mm] hairs on all parts, in particular on both leaf sides (
<quantity box="[582,698,702,723]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="0.3" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.5 mm</quantity>
long in the other Thai taxa).
</paragraph>
